<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-07-23T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-07-23T13:00:00-05:00" n="66" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d66">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">890.00/7–2349: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Douglas</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-07-23T19:00:00+01:00">July 23,
                                    1949—7 p. m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received July 23—6:05 p. m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2910. Bevin has informed me that he is very willing that British and US
                            officials should consult together on the problems dealt with in Deptel
                            2516, July 20 and Embtel 2881, July 22. He suggests that <pb facs="0063" n="53" xml:id="pg_53"/> these talks be carried on while he is away
                            and that when he comes back he will look into the question further with
                            me. Will keep you advised. Is this what you wish?</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Douglas</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>